      <aside class="calc-sidebar">
        <div class="card sidebar-card">
          <h2>What is a bill splitter?</h2>
          <p>A bill splitter calculator divides a restaurant or group bill equally between a number of people, optionally including a tip. It tells each person exactly how much they owe, making it easy to settle up at the end of a meal.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card sidebar-card">
          <h3>Frequently asked questions</h3>
          <details>
            <summary>How do I split a bill with tip included?</summary>
            <p>Add the tip percentage to the total first, then divide by the number of people. For example, £100 bill with 15% tip = £115 total ÷ 4 people = £28.75 each.</p>
          </details>
          <details>
            <summary>What if people ordered different amounts?</summary>
            <p>This calculator splits the bill equally. For unequal splits, each person should pay what they ordered plus a proportional share of the tip.</p>
          </details>
          <details>
            <summary>Should the tip be calculated before or after splitting?</summary>
            <p>Calculate the total including tip first, then divide. This calculator does this automatically.</p>
